📍Trees of Mystery Trails 
Klamath , CA ( on US route 101) 

💫must do attraction if you are road-tripping to redwood national &state park ! Specially recommend it for kids 🤗 ! 
💫admission was 25$ for adults and 13$ for kids ( it includes gondola ride as well ) 
💫dogs allowed with leash except on the redwood canopy trail 
💫The 2 Other easy educational trails were The kingdom of trees trail And Trail of tall tales ! Although my favorite was the redwood canopy and (wilderness trail)! For the wilderness trail , make sure to wear proper hiking shoes . It is very steep coming down most of the way with a rope you can hang on! 🙌

Have you guys been here ? I highly recommend it if you haven’t yet 🙌

📍Fern Canyon 
Prairie Creek Redwood State Park 
Orick , California ! 

💫around 1 mile loop @alltrails ! easy and a unique hike (we walked through the canyon and decided to come back through it since we wanted to experience it more🤗) 
💫The trailhead has bathrooms and beach access 
💫Dogs are not allowed on trails in Prairie Creek Redwoods State Park
💫Permit required to hike from may 1 through sept 30! Must be reserved ahead of time online !!! ( you can either reserve 90 days ahead or day before @0800 (where they give 100 permits each day per website ) I got lucky and got it ! I did it right on time @0801 and there were 50 spots left ! So I would recommend to do it ahead since it’s more busier in summer! 
💫have $12 cash handy ( only cash accepted at the gate ) or if you have the americas beautiful pass ! 
💫 You will have to drive in dirt road and cross two streams ( depending on how much it rains ) to get to trailhead parking lot ! Always check their website ahead 
💫 highly recommend wearing water sandals or waterproof boots ! 

My kids loved getting their feet wet in the stream ! By far their favorite hike 🥰 🙌 
**As always please keep our parks clean and leave it better than you found it ** 🙏🙏

((Did you know part of Jurassic park 2 was filmed here as well ?)) 😊 

.
.

📍Redwood Skywalk in Sequoia Park Zoo 
Eureka , CA ! 

💫100 feet up and nearly 1/4 mile long, this is the longest skywalk in the western U.S. where you can see forest high above from the trees ! 
💫admission price was $12.95 for kids and $24.95 for adults ( admission includes both for zoo and redwood skyline ) 
💫 Mind you this is a small zoo with a petting area for smaller kids. 
💫There are no stairs, so the experience is ADA accessible with the exception of one optional 369-foot adventure segment with open mesh decking! 

Fact: Did you know Sequoia Park Zoo is the oldest zoo in California and one of the smallest accredited zoos in the country? 🤗

We stayed at this lodge for 2 nights and the water park were included with the stay ! 
💫Heated indoor water park featuring a variety of water slides, ( big and smaller ones for lil ones ) , tube slides, raft rides, lazy river , and a wave pool , indoor and outdoor pool as well ! 
💫They had rope course , bowling , mini golfing area, mirror maze which was extra charge of 150$ total for 4 of us ! 
💫They had few dining options including ( breakfast buffet ) , Dunkin’  donuts 🍩but the lines were so long ! luckily there’s plenty of other restaurants nearby outside the hotel ! Also there’s no microwave in the room , but there’s vending machine room in the hallway with a microwave in there ! 
💫Check in at 4 pm but you can come early and start check in process and start playing in park from 1 pm until your room is ready and checkout at 11 am but you can play in park till it closes at 8 pm ! 
💫There are other activities dance parties, storytime, morning yoga, and arts&craft projects , character appearances at the main lobby area at certain times ! 

Overall it was a great pricy experience and my daughter didn’t want to leave 😂! All to celebrate her bday ! ( she was actually shocked at first and said we are not going hiking during the day ??) 😂

📍The Bulb !
Albany , CA 

💫This is a family friendly walk by the bay around 2 mile easy trail ! Small Beach right near the trailhead ! Picnic table and bathroom also available! 
💫small parking lot and you can also park along the road side. Parking lot gets filled up fast on weekends ! 
💫Dog friendly 🤗 
💫So many cool art along the way , wildflowers , beautiful bay view , Rocky in some areas ! Recommend going on a low tide. 

A very unique trail which was once a dumping ground now turned into this cool art !

📍Boy Scout Tree Trail 
Jedediah state redwood state park , CA! 

💫Around 5.3 miles RT moderately challenging hike (@alltrails )among huge ferns and old growth redwoods! It’s so beautiful and my favorite!!! Pictures and videos don’t do any justice honestly! 
💫parking lot at the trailhead with restroom 🚻 (prepare yourself to drive through a dirt /windy road till trailhead ! )
💫pups not allowed ! 
💫family/ kid friendly , not too steep ! The distance might be too far for younger kids. 
💫Small waterfall (Fern fall) at the end ! We rested there and ate snacks . Also , Don’t miss the Boy Scout Tree towards the end ! It’s Huge ! 

If you are looking for a longer forest hike in the Redwood National Park, I would recommend this trail ! Loved every sec of it ! 

**As always please leave no trace and always leave it better than you found it 🙏***

📍Tall Trees Grove Trail 
Redwood National Park, CA ! 

💫Around 3.2 miles RT moderately challenging hike @alltrails . There’s a steep drop going into the grove and a climb returning back ! It will take about half day for this hike , specially with kids maybe longer ☺️ ! 
💫Permit required to hike here on this trail , reserve it 24-48 hours ahead online ! There is a locked gate at the top of the road and the gate code will be emailed to you with your reservation. Once you get in , it’s about 
6 mile drive down a dusty narrow road to the parking lot ! There is a restroom 🚻 as well ! 
💫 We hiked down to the grove and spend some time there by the creek , ate snacks ! Also with a backcountry camping permit, you can even camp anywhere along the creek! It was beautiful and relaxing 😌 
💫pups are not allowed 
💫If you are short on time , there’s lady bird Johnson grove trail ( an easy hike ) nearby. 

If I had to choose between tall tree grove and Boy Scout tree trail , I would definitely choose Boy Scout trail ! 🤗

**please always leave no trace and leave it better than you found it ** #leavenotrace

📍Dimond Canyon Bridgeview Trail 
Near Oakland , CA ! 

💫Easy 1.7 miles RT @alltrails 
💫Nicely shaded trail with lots of trolls on the trail ! ( my kids had so much fun the whole way ) we counted maybe around 30 or even more I think ! 
💫Few rope swings to play around as well ! 
💫No parking lot ! park on the street ! No restroom ! 
💫pups allowed 🤗 

Overall a fun and adventurous hike for the whole family ! Definitely recommend it ! Thank you @cal.euphoria for sharing 🤗

📍Redwood National & State Park 
California! #bestroadtrip 

Our trip itinerary below ⬇️ 

💫Day 1 - Drive from Home (East Bay ) and it took about 5-6 hours ! We also stopped at the Avenue of Giants on our way to Redwood national park ! Enjoy the most scenic drive in the world among huge redwoods ! 
💫Day 2- Hike boyscout tree trail!! ( will take more than  Half day )! we rested in the hotel after this long hike and we always look for hotels with a pool so kids can enjoy 
💫Day 3- Hike Big Trees Trail in the morning and hike fern canyon in the afternoon ( which is pretty short hike ) You can also do the lady bird Johnson grove trail near by ( easy hike ) if you don’t have reservation for the fern canyon ! 
💫Day 4- Go to Trees of Mystery Trails in the morning and we also went to Sequoia Park Zoo in the evening returning back to hotel ! 
Day 5-  Return home 🏡 ( don’t forget to stop by the Bigfoot gift shop on your way home ) 

we stayed in Arcata (holiday inn express ) towards eureka and To get to all these parks , it takes about 35-40 min drive from our hotel! So once you drive towards the park there’s no way we could drive back and forth ! Specially with kids !  Take snacks or lunch ahead ! There are no restaurants or gas stations in the park , so fuel up in one of the towns before !!

📍Children’s Fairyland 
Oakland, CA! 

💫we love visiting fairyland from time to time ! It’s great for toddlers and ideal for ages below 8! Summer hours are open 7days a week from 10-4pm ! 
💫entrance was $16 for age 1 yr and above ( includes the rides and puppet shows) the rides were more suitable for younger child ! 
💫we purchased the magic key 🔑 for $3 and it unlocks audio stories and songs throughout the park ! You can also reuse it on your next visit ! 
💫we came around 2pm and parking was only $3! 

It’s such a cute place to visit 🤗 and my kids have a blast everytime we go there ! #summerbreak

📍Moro Rock Trail 
Sequoia National Park, CA! 

My most fav trail in sequoia!! 

💫short but moderately challenging rated @alltrails ( 350 stairs to the top ) but you will be rewarded with breathtaking views ! 
💫pups not allowed 
💫free shuttle till trailhead during summer and on holidays in the park ( they won’t allow private vehicles) so shuttles are your only transportation! ( check website ahead) 
💫restrooms near trailhead ! 

Have you checked this off if your bucket list ? Highly recommend it🤗

📍Mystery Spot 
Santa Cruz , CA! 

💫Fun attraction for the whole family if you are near the area! $ 10 per person , age 3 and below are free ! 
💫parking cost $5 ! 
💫Reserve tickets ahead online specially during summer time and on holidays! I reserved it a day ahead and it was sold out in the morning already , so had to book one around afternoon ! 
💫Short hiking trail next to the parking lot ! We were there lil early so we hit the trail first while waiting for our tour ! 
💫They have gift shop , restrooms, and a snack shack inside ! 

Have you guys been there yet ! I’ve been here in the bay  for the longest and this was our first time here 🙌 and enjoyed it also !

📍Rancho San Antonio open space preserve , Santa Clara county CA! 

💫we did the (Lower meadow trail to farm bypass loop) trail , popular for biking , hiking , running! 
💫first mile was open and hot but it gets more shaded and there was a small stream to cool off as well ! 
💫you can opt to do one mile flat wheelchair/ stroller accessible to Deer Hollow Farm ! You can visit cows, sheep, goats, chickens, ducks and pigs! Check their website for hours ! 
💫pups not allowed 
💫weekends are mostly crowded as always ! 
💫don’t forget to bring a hat and apply sunscreen, it was hot 🥵! 

Overall perfect for kids ! 🤗

📍Pillar point bluff trail 
San Mateo County , CA ! 

💫we did pillar point bluff to Ross cove beach around less than 3 miles easy trail ! 
💫we found this trail from POST’s (find your place) and navigated from there to get to trailhead . 
💫small parking lot where we started , Restroom available at trailhead ! 
💫beautiful coastal trail with lots of wildflowers 
💫pups allowed with leash on trail but not on beach ! 
💫we sighted bunch of 🦭 seals! and kids loved it even more ! highly recommend this trail and has become one of my favorite coastal trails 🤗 

If you are interested in finding trails like this check out Openspacetrust.org  #postlands 

**please follow leave no trace and leave it better than you found it 🙏

📍COWELL-PURISIMA COASTAL TRAiL 
Half Moon Bay , CA ! 

💫Around  3.6 mile one way , easy trail near the coast! 
💫There is parking available at this trail’s northern and southern trailheads. 
💫restrooms available at both parking lots and the southern bathroom is wheelchair accessible. Use the northern trailhead for access to the Cowell Ranch Beach! 
💫watch out for harbor seals, pelicans, hawks and wildflowers along the way. It was such a beautiful trail and so thankful I found this trail on @postlandtrust 

🙏as always leave no trace !! Happy trails 🥾

📍 Máyyan 'Ooyákma - Coyote Ridge Open Space Preserve! 
(Santa Clara , CA) 

Thank you so much @open_space_authority for the invitation to celebrate the opening of this beautiful preserve ! 

🦋 Due to its sensitive habitat, the visitor experience at this preserve will be unlike any other, with a Butterfly Pass, special hours, and (free) reservations required during wildflower season!!! Getting a butterfly pass 🦋 is free and easy , simply visit their website and agree to follow the preserve rules and download your pass ! 
Link : bit.Ly/butterfly-pass-2023 
Your butterfly pass is good for rest of the year ☺️ ! 

Trails to explore ; 
🌸Mayyan Waayi (Coyote valley) overlook trail - ADA accessible 
🌸Serpentine Spring trail 
🌸Tule Elk Trail 
🌸Bay Checkerspot Trail 

Am so thankful to enjoy this beautiful new preserve at sunset and can’t wait to check it out during spring time ! 

Please #leavenotrace 🙏🙏 and let’s enjoy responsibly!

Hi guys! I am excited to share this free tool (Find Your Place) to search your next hike! 

Created by POST (Peninsula Open Space Trust - @postlandtrust), a non profit organization located in the Bay Area! Their mission is to protect open spaces where people and nature connect and thrive.

We found this beautiful shaded hike in this tool and definitely recommend using it! 📍Truind trek 
Dharamshala, India 

💫Around 11.8 miles RT rated hard @alltrails 
💫There are two main Triund trek routes: One from Dharamkot (via Gallu Devi Temple) and one from McLeodganj (via Bhagsu) ! we started from Dharamkot ! 
💫you will meet plenty of people on the trail, and it’s easy to navigate . However, you can also hire a trek guide but you don’t necessarily need it ! 
💫 It was pretty much uphill most of the way and steep at times ! There were few chai shops on the way to take breaks ! 
💫you can camp overnight at the top (no reservations required ! ) which I recommend if you have more time , you can also hike up more to glacier point ! I only did a day trip with limited time ! 
💫 There’s also a shop on the top where you can buy tea and snacks ! Bring cash 🙌 

The view at the Top was breathtaking! I’ve done this back in 9th grade and to do this all over again was just mind blowing! An Experience that I will never forget 🙌

📍Keough’s Hot Spring
Bishop , California 

💫Keough’s Hot Springs have a large pool kept at 88–90 degrees year round; and a smaller hot pool at 104 degrees year round.!! The Pools are emptied, cleaned and then filled again each week. Both pools are free flowing pools so they have a constant flow of fresh mineral water throughout the day.
💫Besides the pools, they have dressing rooms and restrooms, and lounge chairs surround the pools for sitting and sunbathing( bring your own towel ) ! 
💫They also have a gift shop stocked with swimming supplies  and camping accessories! 
💫parking was free ! 
💫Tickets cost Adults : $14 and child (3-12): $10

They also have RV& Camp sites and a rock garden trail ! I would definitely camp here next time! Kids had such a great time ! Such a gem in the sierras! Especially after a long day it was so relaxing and soothing in the hot spring 🤗

Hi guys ! 
As much as I’ve  been promoting to get outside in nature I also wanted to share some basic trail etiquette for all the new hikers !  Knowing these basic trail etiquette is so important because it allows everyone to enjoy the outdoors responsibly and have a good time while being safe and courteous😊

1- Know your right of way
***Hikers coming uphill have the right of way!! So if you are descending, always yield on side for the people coming uphill ! 
***Bicyclists yield to hikers and horses ! 
***Hikers yield to horses ! 

2- Stay on the Trail
While hiking, be mindful and stay on the trail to avoid damaging the surrounding environment and leave the area just as you found it ! Don’t take shortcuts!

3- Keep Your Distance from Wildlife 
Not only it’s dangerous, it’s illegal in most places ! 

4- Always Be Considerate of other hikers 
Don’t blast music. Most of us come out in nature for peace, quietness and away from any noise pollution ! If you want to listen to music,  try using a single earbud or keeping the volume low so you can hear approaching hikers, runners, or cyclists. And most importantly, Yelling / loud noise can cause panic or disruption to wildlife ! They rely on these natural sounds for survival ! 

5- Leave No Trace!! 
This is one of the most IMPORTANT hiking etiquette rules. (This means leaving the trail and surrounding environment exactly as you found it, or even better. Pack in , pack out ( includes even orange peels!!) Avoid damaging vegetation, disturbing wildlife, or leaving any kind of markings on the trail) 🙏🙏

And lastly Treat other hikers with kindness, respect , and without judgement. Outdoors is for everyone ! Most of the hikers I’ve met on trails are the nicest people I’ve encountered! 🙏 

Hiking etiquette is all about respecting the environment and other hikers on the trail. By following these basic rules, you can help ensure a safe and enjoyable hiking experience for everyone. 🤗 #happytrails 🥾

📍Phantom falls 
(oroville , CA) 

💫Part of North Table Mountain Ecological Reserve
and you Need to get a Lands Pass online to hike ( it’s easy to get it online) 
💫around 4.1 miles RT rated moderately challenging in @alltrails alltrails app! Rocky  in some areas so wear proper shoes ! Trails not well marked , I suggest downloading the trail map ahead ! 
💫open year around / best in spring with wildflowers blooming ! Although when we went there it snowed which was a unique experience 🤩( this was in Feb ) 
💫pups allowed with leash 
💫check out ravine falls on the way to phantom falls

📍skunk train (Rail bike - pudding creek express ! ) 
Mendocino, CA ! 

💫Enjoy this Electric-powered, 2- person railbike that takes you along the world-famous Redwood Route. We did the pudding express ( it’s about 20 minutes ride each way ) Then you get to rest at Glen Blair Junction for a 50-minute layover to enjoy a picnic or explore easy trails around ! 
**you can also do the longer version ( rail bikes on the Noyo) **
💫kids must be 3 yrs and up / adjustable seat ! They don’t really have to pedal and no, it’s not tiring at all ! They also provide helmets ( or bring your own ) ! 
💫Dog trailers and crates are now available for your dogs (total weight) up to 150 pounds. Bring your furry friend so they can also enjoy 😊 
💫must wear closed toe shoes and also bring a jacket , it is kinda chilly ! 
💫Bring snacks and water 
💫Rate is $265.00 per bike, with room for two riders. 
It is pretty expensive but definitely an awesome experience!
